## Conclusion
The path to 1 Million TPS is no longer heavily constrained by architecture. The zero-conflict DAG and ZephyrDB structures are mathematically capable. The remaining work is strictly engineering execution: wiring the components asynchronously, enforcing memory/L1 cache locality, optimizing P2P UDP shredding for 150MB bandwidth, and solidifying the RISC-V execution bridge.
